  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      We hypothesize that topical betaxolol will reduce the development of severe retinopathy of
      prematurity.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The drug is administered twice a day between 32 and 35 weeks gestational age, at a t ime when
      ROP is most likely to arise.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
